                    "ctaUrl": {
                      "value": "/rolex-awards/environment/liu-shaochuang"
                    },
                    "descriptionText": {
                      "value": "Wild camels have roamed the Gobi Desert for thousands of years, but now they are critically endangered. Chinese remote sensing specialist Liu Shaochuang uses satellite technology to monitor herds far more efficiently than traditional tracking methods allow. His findings will be instrumental in establishing two extensive conservation zones across China and Mongolia."
                    },
                    "descriptionTitle": {
                      "value": "Tracking wild camels with satellites"
                    },
                    "imageLandscape_src": {
