                    },
                    "descriptionText": {
                      "value": "In the high Andes, only two per cent of the original forest remains. Peruvian biologist Constantino Aucca Chutas has been working with indigenous communities to reforest the area and to protect its unique ecosystems. Since beginning this project, he has been responsible for planting 4.5 million trees in Peru alone."
